      "blockType": "paragraph",
      "chunkId": "ck_page_news_005_go_118_release_0003",
      "confidence": 0.92,
      "contentHash": "sha256_92d01524b74b84ef97803223c55a9c7dbe023f3364b41cccfafc73cc08075fc5",
      "fallbackText": "Apple M1, ARM64, and PowerPC64 users rejoice! Go 1.18 includes CPU performance improvements of up to 20% due to the expansion of Go 1.17’s register ABI calling convention to these architectures. Just to underscore how big this release is, a 20% performance improvement is the fourth most important headline!",
      "headingPath": [
